'''Spears''' are fast-speed two-handed [[stab]]bing [[weapons]] used in [[melee]] [[combat]]. They are obtained from either [[monster drop]]s, purchasing from players, or [[smithing]] on the special anvil south of the [[Barbarian Outpost]] or [[Barbarian Village]]. Most spears can be [[poison]]ed with normal weapon poisons or [[karambwan paste]].

Although they can only be used to train controlled and defensive attacks, spears are still arguably the most flexible weapons in the game, as they are the only weapon besides the [[Hasta]] to use [[Stab]], [[Crush]], and [[Slash]] [[attack styles]], and their speed gives them damage per second close to that of [[scimitar]]s. However, spears are rarely used as they do not excel in any particular style and other two-handed weapons, such as the [[two-handed sword]] and the [[halberd]] have higher attack bonuses despite being much slower. Its flexibility can be useful for saving inventory space during the [[Spirits of the Elid]] [[Quests|quest]] which requires that all three melee [[attack types]] be used.

Each attack style of the spear, except for Defensive, is Controlled and gives shared melee experience ([[Attack]], [[Strength]], and [[Defence]]). All styles also give [[Hitpoints]] experience.

All spears have an attack speed of 4 [[game tick]]s, except the [[Leaf-bladed spear]] and [[Guthan's warspear]] which have a speed of 5, and the [[Bone spear]], which has a speed of 6. This makes the spear the fastest two-handed weapon type in the game, tied with [[claws]].

== Creation ==
The ability to smith a spear requires completion of the [[Barbarian Training#Barbarian Smithing|Barbarian Smithing]] section of the [[Barbarian Training]] as well as completion of the [[Tai Bwo Wannai Trio]] quest and level 5 [[Smithing]]. 

